      <h1 class='title'>Vehicle Excise Duty Offences</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c66WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_66ws' title='Col. 66WS &mdash; HC Deb 27 October 2003 vol 412 c66WS' name='column_66ws' href='#column_66ws' rel='bookmark'>66WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04912'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_335'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-christopher-chope' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_335' title='Link to this speech by Mr Christopher Chope' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-christopher-chope" title="Mr Christopher Chope">Mr. Chope</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04912">To ask the Secretary of State for Transport how many unlicensed vehicles he estimates the DVLA will<span class="italic">(a)</span> wheel clamp and <span class="italic">(b)</span> crush in 2004. [134748]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0412P0-04913'>
        <a name='S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_336'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-jamieson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0412P0_20031027_CWS2_336' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Jamieson' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-jamieson" title="Mr David Jamieson">Mr. Jamieson</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0412P0-04913">So far in 2003&#x2013;04, DVLA has clamped 46,302 vehicles. In addition, the 14 local authorities that now have devolved powers to clamp and impound on behalf of the Secretary of State have clamped an additional 6,601&#x2014;a total of 52,903. We expect that to rise to 65,000 by the end of the financial year.</p><p id="S6CV0412P0-04914">The number of vehicles crushed by DVLA is 21,144 so far, with the 14 local authorities crushing an additional 3,052&#x2014;a total of 24,196. We expect that figure to rise to 30,000 by the end of the financial year.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
